 that helps best i can do without delving back into my notes later<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Arkstriker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">OH now i remember about eurdin <BR>GEt a whole lota bone chips give invis take them to some one in the Tranquil Cleric's guild and hand in the bone chips raises faction w/the guards and the clerics though you still cant raise faction with the deepwater knights the other paladin guild, (BUgged as of late and probly sind the begining) that quest gives faction with Eurdin and sometime raw hide armor which can be sold for about a plat a piece, rusty blunt weapons, and sometimes a level 1 cleric spell<P>The Striker<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Nilraek Vin'Lottl</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">I am a DE necromancer that worships Innoruuk and am in Crushbone trying to raise my faction with all the NPC's in Kelethin. I was wondering if this it at all possible or am I just waisting my time? I don't want my faction to be just dubious there either, I would like to get it all the way up to warmly.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Rabdos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Qeynos is fairly easy. Go to blackburrow, and cast a siphon strength on every gnoll you see being engaged by somebody. Park your pet near the top of the ramp and derail the massive trains. It'll probably take you about 10 hours to be dubious to Qeynos guards and merchants.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Forbin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Ok I'm a DE Wizard worshiping Solusek Ro<P>Here's what I am<P>I can go everywhere (Yes including all of Felwhite) except <P>1) Halas - Didn't do any quests there yet<BR>2) Scouts of Tunare - Rouges<BR>3) Rivervale Merchants - Guards love me<BR>4) Ogguk Warriors and Clurg - Too much Goonda hunting in WK<BR>5) Wizard Gnomes - Didn't fix this yet.<BR>6) All good bankers - Why are they all rouge faction?  Felwithe doesn't even have a rouge guild.<BR>7) The people in the Seafarers roost in Freeport.  Must be Halas faction<P>BTW: I used the Aqua goblins to get my Elf faction and didn't hurt my Neriak factions, but about an hour in CB hunting Emporer Crush made me Dub in Indigo Brotherhood.  But the slaver quest now lets me shop in Kelethin (Like I really want to)<P><BR>PS : Here are some things that I can do with my faction.  Shop in Kelethin. Shop in Felwithe.  Shop in Freeport and Qyenos.  Say hello to all the dwarfs in Kaladium..hehe<P>Here's what I want to know,<P>1) What's a good way to fix my Indigo and The Dead Faction (I did the Mystic cloak quest and that sacked it) WITHOUT sacking my Elf faction?<P>2) Is there a Kelethin Rouge faction quest?  So I can finally bank there?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Oninoyakamo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Killing Kerrans in Kerra Isle will raise Deepwater Knights faction/Gemcutter, plus a few others</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">cynner8u</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Though I'm a Barbarian, I went and got myself KOS to Qeynos Guards and Surefall Rangers and Residents by massive killing of Treants.<BR>I've been doing the BB thing - area effect DOT and healing a party of newbies to get faction without stealing their xp.<BR>I've also been killing the West Karana Bandits; gives good faction with Highpass and Qeynos guards and Karana Residents.  Who cares if your bandit faction goes down?<BR>Also, the Unkempt Druids in Mt. Rathe.  Though this will lower your faction to the animals of Surefall, it will raise it to the Residents of Surefall and the Qeynos guards.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Shadow313</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Ok, What about getting faction with the Dark Barganers when you are dubious?  I know there is the quest in the third gate that you can give whine to.  There is also the smith in southern ro for the lightstone quest.  But you can't get either to do quests if you are dubious and don't know any other way to gain faction.  I have tried getting someone to turn me into a wolf in S Ro, I have gotten an item to change into a tree (had to train her out of the desert).  I just can't seem to find any way...  Does anyone know any way to gain faction with the dark barganers?   <IMG SRC="http://www.neriak.com/ubb/smile.gif"> please?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Thundarbreath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">To increase faction with heretics I've found the best way to do it is not to kill the erudin guards, doing so will give the following faction adjustments +Heretics, -deepwater knights, -gate callers, -craft keepers and -crimson hands.  Instead go to Freeport docks, swim out to the beach and look for Bait Masterson or his place holder Giz Dintree.  If you are high enough level...kill these two over and over to get the follow faction adjustments: Bait Masterson +Heretics, -High Council of Erudin, -Deepwater Knights...Giz Dintree +Guards of Qeynos, +Wolves of Tunare, +Guardians of the Vale, +Carson McCabe, -Circle of Unseen Hands,-Coalition of Tradefolk, -Corrupt Qeynos Guards.  The spawn rate is about 5 min and gives you enough time to do the note to Janam/Note to Rebby quests in the sewers which helps you to raise faction with freeport militia caolition of tradesfolk 1 and 3 carson mccabe and corrupt qeynos guards.  Still trying to find an easy way to improve faction with circle of unseen hands.<p>[This message has been edited by Thundarbreath (edited March 24, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Thundarbreath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Erudite guards are the way to go if want into paineel...read tactics under the Heretic message section.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Thundarbreath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">If you want into the plaguebringer guild in Qeynos catacombs (most people call this the necro guild but I resent that...I'm a cleric and its my guild too..heh) you will need to raise faction with the bloodsabers.  Here is a couple of people you can kill.  Bait Masterson in Freeport by the docks or in Qeynos Catacombs (sometimes) faction +heretics -high council of erudin -deepwater knights.  Bait Mastersons place holder in freeport is Giz Dintree +gurads of Qeynos, +Wolves of North, +Guardians of the vale, +Carson MacCabe -Ebon Mask (monks?).  His placeholder in catacombs i think is a skeleton.  In West Karanas, just as you zone in from Qeynos hills and come out of the mountain pass you will see 1 or 2 clerics.  Killing Brother Estle or Brother Chintle +bloodsabers -priests of life, -knights of thunder, -guars of qeynos -antonius bayle (this guy really hates me).  There is a third Brother that shows up, he is secretly a bloodsaber, killing him will not destroy your faction with the bloodsabers and is often necessary if you are gonna camp there for awhile killing the clerics.  His name is Brother Trintle.  If you camp there you will notice every once and awhile some npc will run by you.  I decided to see what factions these guy had...guess what +bloodsabers -priest of life -knights of truth -guards of qeynos -antonius bayle (some of their names are tolony marle, habastash giki, kyle rinlin, gomo limerin, greblin sneztop i think its a random name generator).  After killing these guys i suggest you head to black burrow for a little bit and kill gnolls to improve faction with qeynos guards.  There is also a high level cleric in North Karanas called Brother Nallin, blue at lvl 38, I'm afraid to kill him cause he spawns near the white bridge where all the guards like to hang out.  Another cleric is in South Karanas called Brother Drash (looks like a splitpaw gnoll) +bloodsabers, -priests of life, -knights of thunder -guards of qeynos, -antonius bayle.  In qeynos newbie area there is a guy named Lashun Novashine killing him also same factions as the clerics. Qeynos Hills killing Neclo Rheslar +bloodsabers +opal darkbriar -guards of qeynos -order of three (some kind of wizard guild).  Be prepared to kill lots and lots of these guys.  Im a bloodsaber and have killed probably close to 50 of them and my faction with my guild is still only amiable...probably cause ive had to kill some bloodsabers along the way to figure out who to kill and who not to kill.  Let me know forget Milea Clothspinner in East Karanas in the gorge on the way to HPH.  +Bloodsabers, +Opal Dark Briar, +Corrupt Qeynos Guards -Priests of Life, -Guards of Qeynos.  She drops a veil that you can give to one of the clerics in the bloodsaber guild for some experience.  Actually, if you are in Freeport there is a quest involving Milea called hopeless love on alakazams website where you deliver a message from her lover +steel warriors, +guards of qeynos, +knights of truth -corrupt guards of qeynos -freeport militia.  Then you simply kill her and bring her veil to the bloodsabers.  Now for people you don't want to kill...dont kill necros in general...although Im not sure about some of them...I think the necros out in Rathe Mountains might be fair game, but dont quote me on this one.  Don't kill the skeleton guards in Qeynos Catacombs +Guards of Qeynos +Priests of Life, -Bloodsabers -Opal Dark Briar -Corrupt Qeynos Guards.  In Qeynos hills dont kill Tovax Vmar or Pyzjin (same factions as above).  Some Qeynos guards are corrupt...killing them +guards of qeynos, -corrupt qeynos guards -bloodsabers -kane bayle -circle of unseen hands (i think this is qeynos rogue guild, generally you want a good faction with any rogues).  If anyone has any additions to this list please let me know.  I would like to get my faction back up to warmly or kindly with my guild to see if they have installed any new quests (wishful thinking).</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
